title: Roundup: Watts' goal lifts Notre Dame over Highlands
text:
Roundup: Watts' goal lifts Notre Dame over Highlands Cincinnati 11:01 p.m. EDT October 21, 2015 Buy Photo Notre Dame's Taylor Watts scored the only goal in the Pandas' win over Highlands on Wednesday. (Photo: The Community Recorder/James Weber/The Community Recorder) Buy Photo 
Senior forward Taylor Watts scored the game-winning goal as Notre Dame Academy defeated Highlands 1-0 in a Ninth Region tournament semifinal game Wednesday, to give the Pandas their eighteenth win of the season. 
Junior goalkeeper, Audrey Nienaber, earned the shutout. 
Campbell County 7, Harrison County 0: Seniors Olivia Nelson and Taylor Jolly both scored twice and goalkeepers Taylor Peterson and Hannah Anderson combined to make four saves in the shutout. 
Natalie Fausz, Lindsey Brown and Ashley Schreiber also scored goals in the victory. 
Ohio 
Boys' soccer 
Indian Hill 3, Batavia 0: The Braves collected goals from seniors Carter Hoffman, Casey McClay and Jake Young and senior goalkeeper Robby Green earned the clean sheet as Indian Hill won their sectional opener. 
Indian Hill advances to face Waynesville on Saturday at Indian Hill at 7 p.m. 
Mariemont 3, Ross 0: Senior Matthew Teeters earned the shutout while Andrew Brandser, Connor Jacob and Jack Mathis all scored goal in the Warriors' sectional-tournament opening win. 
Mariemont advances to play Goshen on Saturday at Mariemont at 7 p.m. Read or Share this story: http://cin.ci/1RXtyI8 TOP VIDEOS
